                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-09-10</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Extremely well organized and presented in an easy-to-grasp way, Hacking Windows 2000 Exposed will have the novice's jaws dropping, yet even the seasoned Win2K expert will raise an eyebrow (or both). The latest hacks and cracks are explained in detail, allowing the admin to really and truly see what they are up against and why security is so important to ANY computer attached to a network. I highly recommend that before you attach a Windows 2000 system to the Internet, read this book and test your system's security fully -- before an unwanted intruder does.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Buy this book if you use windows</div>
